Class TopicDefinitionInterpreter

All Implemented Interfaces:
IExpressionInterpreter<TopicDefinition>
public class TopicDefinitionInterpreter
extends ExpressionInterpreterImpl<TopicDefinition>

Special implementation of ExpressionInterpreterImpl representing the interpreter of a topic-definition as a kind of update-clauses.

The grammar production rule of the expression is:

topic-definition ::= string-literal ( ! | ~ | = ) topic-definition ::= string-literal << ( item | locators | indicators )

Author:
Sven Krosse
